{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-8fad1bb70cc8ad8e", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# Step-Audio 2 Technical Report\narXiv: 2507.16632\nAuthors: Boyong Wu, Chao Yan, Chen Hu, Cheng Yi, Chengli Feng, Fei Tian, Feiyu Shen, Gang Yu, Haoyang Zhang, Jingbei Li, Mingrui Chen, Peng Liu, Wang You, Xiangyu Tony Zhang, Xingyuan Li, Xuerui Yang, Yayue Deng, Yechang Huang, Yuxin Li, Yuxin Zhang, Zhao You, Brian Li, Changyi Wan, Hanpeng Hu, Jiangjie Zhen, Siyu Chen, Song Yuan, Xuelin Zhang, Yimin Jiang, Yu Zhou, Yuxiang Yang, Bingxin Li, Buyun Ma, Changhe Song, Dongqing Pang, Guoqiang Hu, Haiyang Sun, Kang An, Na Wang, Shuli Gao, Wei Ji, Wen Li, Wen Sun, Xuan Wen, Yong Ren, Yuankai Ma, Yufan Lu, Bin Wang, Bo Li, Changxin Miao, Che Liu, Chen Xu, Dapeng Shi, Dingyuan Hu, Donghang Wu, Enle Liu, Guanzhe Huang, Gulin Yan, Han Zhang, Hao Nie, Haonan Jia, Hongyu Zhou, Jianjian Sun, Jiaoren Wu, Jie Wu, Jie Yang, Jin Yang, Junzhe Lin, Kaixiang Li, Lei Yang, Liying Shi, Li Zhou, Longlong Gu, Ming Li, Mingliang Li, Mingxiao Li, Nan Wu, Qi Han, Qinyuan Tan, Shaoliang Pang, Shengjie Fan, Siqi Liu, Tiancheng Cao, Wanying Lu, Wenqing He, Wuxun Xie, Xu Zhao, Xueqi Li, Yanbo Yu, Yang Yang, Yi Liu, Yifan Lu, Yilei Wang, Yuanhao Ding, Yuanwei Liang, Yuanwei Lu, Yuchu Luo, Yuhe Yin, Yumeng Zhan, Yuxiang Zhang, Zidong Yang, Zixin Zhang, Binxing Jiao, Daxin Jiang, Heung-Yeung Shum, Jiansheng Chen, Jing Li, Xiangyu Zhang, Yibo Zhu\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: audio_understanding\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Integrates discrete audio token generation into language modeling to achieve genuine end-to-end speech conversation and enhance responsiveness to paralinguistic information.\n  2. Leverages a latent audio encoder and reasoning-centric reinforcement learning to improve speech and audio understanding.\n  3. Incorporates retrieval-augmented generation and external tool calling, including a novel audio search tool for timbre and speaking style switching, to mitigate hallucination and leverage real-world knowledge.\n  4. Develops a multi-stage training strategy trained on millions of hours of diverse audio and textual data to ensure robust intelligence and expressiveness.\n  5. Introduces new evaluation benchmarks for paralinguistic understanding and tool calling to assess complex audio interaction capabilities.\n  6. Achieves state-of-the-art performance across multiple audio understanding and speech conversation benchmarks, outperforming existing open-source and commercial solutions.\n\nTags: LALM/音频标记-融合, LALM/对话型-交错标记, LALM/后训练-GRPO, LALM/训练-指令微调", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "41de9cbc-b65e-4e09-af8e-e10262dbf093", "uuid": "0d6d9cd0-60b7-42ba-be95-e05ea3cd5498", "timestamp": "2026-07-11T12:18:43.963Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# Step-Audio 2 Technical Report\narXiv: 2507.16632\nAuthors: Boyong Wu, Chao Yan, Chen Hu, Cheng Yi, Chengli Feng, Fei Tian, Feiyu Shen, Gang Yu, Haoyang Zhang, Jingbei Li, Mingrui Chen, Peng Liu, Wang You, Xiangyu Tony Zhang, Xingyuan Li, Xuerui Yang, Yayue Deng, Yechang Huang, Yuxin Li, Yuxin Zhang, Zhao You, Brian Li, Changyi Wan, Hanpeng Hu, Jiangjie Zhen, Siyu Chen, Song Yuan, Xuelin Zhang, Yimin Jiang, Yu Zhou, Yuxiang Yang, Bingxin Li, Buyun Ma, Changhe Song, Dongqing Pang, Guoqiang Hu, Haiyang Sun, Kang An, Na Wang, Shuli Gao, Wei Ji, Wen Li, Wen Sun, Xuan Wen, Yong Ren, Yuankai Ma, Yufan Lu, Bin Wang, Bo Li, Changxin Miao, Che Liu, Chen Xu, Dapeng Shi, Dingyuan Hu, Donghang Wu, Enle Liu, Guanzhe Huang, Gulin Yan, Han Zhang, Hao Nie, Haonan Jia, Hongyu Zhou, Jianjian Sun, Jiaoren Wu, Jie Wu, Jie Yang, Jin Yang, Junzhe Lin, Kaixiang Li, Lei Yang, Liying Shi, Li Zhou, Longlong Gu, Ming Li, Mingliang Li, Mingxiao Li, Nan Wu, Qi Han, Qinyuan Tan, Shaoliang Pang, Shengjie Fan, Siqi Liu, Tiancheng Cao, Wanying Lu, Wenqing He, Wuxun Xie, Xu Zhao, Xueqi Li, Yanbo Yu, Yang Yang, Yi Liu, Yifan Lu, Yilei Wang, Yuanhao Ding, Yuanwei Liang, Yuanwei Lu, Yuchu Luo, Yuhe Yin, Yumeng Zhan, Yuxiang Zhang, Zidong Yang, Zixin Zhang, Binxing Jiao, Daxin Jiang, Heung-Yeung Shum, Jiansheng Chen, Jing Li, Xiangyu Zhang, Yibo Zhu\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: audio_understanding\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Integrates discrete audio token generation into language modeling to achieve genuine end-to-end speech conversation and enhance responsiveness to paralinguistic information.\n  2. Leverages a latent audio encoder and reasoning-centric reinforcement learning to improve speech and audio understanding.\n  3. Incorporates retrieval-augmented generation and external tool calling, including a novel audio search tool for timbre and speaking style switching, to mitigate hallucination and leverage real-world knowledge.\n  4. Develops a multi-stage training strategy trained on millions of hours of diverse audio and textual data to ensure robust intelligence and expressiveness.\n  5. Introduces new evaluation benchmarks for paralinguistic understanding and tool calling to assess complex audio interaction capabilities.\n  6. Achieves state-of-the-art performance across multiple audio understanding and speech conversation benchmarks, outperforming existing open-source and commercial solutions.\n\nTags: LALM/音频标记-融合, LALM/对话型-交错标记, LALM/后训练-GRPO, LALM/训练-指令微调", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-8099a6c77cf127a4", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# Audio-DeepThinker: Progressive Reasoning-Aware Reinforcement Learning for High-Quality Chain-of-Thought Emergence in Audio Language Models\narXiv: 2604.18187\nAuthors: Xiang He, Chenxing Li, Jinting Wang, Yan Rong, Tianxin Xie, Wenfu Wang, Li Liu, Dong Yu\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: audio_understanding\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose a hybrid reasoning similarity reward that directly supervises the quality of generated reasoning chains by combining LLM-based logical evaluation with embedding-based semantic alignment, jointly addressing the dual challenges of reasoning soundness and audio grounding.\n  2. We demonstrate that high-quality CoT reasoning can emerge through pure RL exploration from an instruction-tuned LALM without prior chain-of-thought capability, enabled by a progressive two-stage curriculum that establishes foundational patterns and then refines them on challenging boundary cases.\n  3. Audio-DeepThinker achieves state-of-the-art results on MMAR, MMAU-test-mini, and MMSU, winning 1st Place in the Single Model Track of the Interspeech 2026 Audio Reasoning Challenge.\n  4. Mechanistic interpretability analyses reveal that RL training primarily reshapes upper-layer MoE gating mechanisms and that reasoning tokens crystallize progressively in the upper transformer layers, providing novel insights into how audio reasoning capabilities are acquired through exploration.\n\nTags: LALM, LALM/理解型, LALM/后训练-GRPO", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "41de9cbc-b65e-4e09-af8e-e10262dbf093", "uuid": "a3f93221-a3ab-42dc-bba3-fc1d28954f49", "timestamp": "2026-07-11T12:18:44.194Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# Audio-DeepThinker: Progressive Reasoning-Aware Reinforcement Learning for High-Quality Chain-of-Thought Emergence in Audio Language Models\narXiv: 2604.18187\nAuthors: Xiang He, Chenxing Li, Jinting Wang, Yan Rong, Tianxin Xie, Wenfu Wang, Li Liu, Dong Yu\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: audio_understanding\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose a hybrid reasoning similarity reward that directly supervises the quality of generated reasoning chains by combining LLM-based logical evaluation with embedding-based semantic alignment, jointly addressing the dual challenges of reasoning soundness and audio grounding.\n  2. We demonstrate that high-quality CoT reasoning can emerge through pure RL exploration from an instruction-tuned LALM without prior chain-of-thought capability, enabled by a progressive two-stage curriculum that establishes foundational patterns and then refines them on challenging boundary cases.\n  3. Audio-DeepThinker achieves state-of-the-art results on MMAR, MMAU-test-mini, and MMSU, winning 1st Place in the Single Model Track of the Interspeech 2026 Audio Reasoning Challenge.\n  4. Mechanistic interpretability analyses reveal that RL training primarily reshapes upper-layer MoE gating mechanisms and that reasoning tokens crystallize progressively in the upper transformer layers, providing novel insights into how audio reasoning capabilities are acquired through exploration.\n\nTags: LALM, LALM/理解型, LALM/后训练-GRPO", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-bef22b50961372e6", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# GSRM: Generative Speech Reward Model for Speech RLHF\narXiv: 2602.13891\nAuthors: Maohao Shen, Tejas Jayashankar, Osama Hanna, Naoyuki Kanda, Yancheng Wang, Kateřina Žmolíková, Ruiming Xie, Niko Moritz, Anfeng Xu, Yashesh Gaur, Gregory Wornell, Qing He, Jilong Wu\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_other\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Curation of a large-scale human feedback dataset for speech naturalness, comprising 31k expert ratings on conversational TTS and an out-of-domain benchmark of real-world user-assistant speech interactions.\n  2. Introduction of a Generative Speech Reward Model (GSRM) that decomposes speech naturalness evaluation into interpretable acoustic feature extraction followed by feature-grounded chain-of-thought reasoning.\n  3. Development of a scalable CoT synthesis pipeline that generates high-quality reasoning trajectories by grounding textual logic in explicitly extracted paralinguistic acoustic cues.\n  4. Demonstration that GSRM substantially outperforms existing speech naturalness predictors, achieving model-human correlation that approaches human inter-rater consistency.\n  5. First application of an online RLHF framework to improve the naturalness of a full-duplex speech LLM by leveraging GSRM as a reward verifier.\n\nTags: LALM, LALM/后训练-GRPO, Eval, Eval/听觉感知", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "41de9cbc-b65e-4e09-af8e-e10262dbf093", "uuid": "19c1caee-9951-4c84-a835-ce9adc319933", "timestamp": "2026-07-11T12:18:44.413Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# GSRM: Generative Speech Reward Model for Speech RLHF\narXiv: 2602.13891\nAuthors: Maohao Shen, Tejas Jayashankar, Osama Hanna, Naoyuki Kanda, Yancheng Wang, Kateřina Žmolíková, Ruiming Xie, Niko Moritz, Anfeng Xu, Yashesh Gaur, Gregory Wornell, Qing He, Jilong Wu\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_other\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Curation of a large-scale human feedback dataset for speech naturalness, comprising 31k expert ratings on conversational TTS and an out-of-domain benchmark of real-world user-assistant speech interactions.\n  2. Introduction of a Generative Speech Reward Model (GSRM) that decomposes speech naturalness evaluation into interpretable acoustic feature extraction followed by feature-grounded chain-of-thought reasoning.\n  3. Development of a scalable CoT synthesis pipeline that generates high-quality reasoning trajectories by grounding textual logic in explicitly extracted paralinguistic acoustic cues.\n  4. Demonstration that GSRM substantially outperforms existing speech naturalness predictors, achieving model-human correlation that approaches human inter-rater consistency.\n  5. First application of an online RLHF framework to improve the naturalness of a full-duplex speech LLM by leveraging GSRM as a reward verifier.\n\nTags: LALM, LALM/后训练-GRPO, Eval, Eval/听觉感知", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
